A RESOLUTION
1 Commending the Georgia Young Farmer Teacher Program; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, the Georgia Young Farmer Teacher Program (GYFT) provides systematic
3 agricultural education for individuals actively engaged in farming or agricultural endeavors;
4 and
5 WHEREAS, the program operates under the direction of the State Department of Education
6 and local agriculture departments in public high schools, with instruction planned jointly by
7 Young Farmer Teachers and participants; and
8 WHEREAS, the GYFT was established in 1951 as an instructional initiative coordinated by
9 full-time Young Farmer Teachers and expanded in 1971 with the organization of the Georgia
10 Young Farmers Association to provide state-level coordination and leadership activities; and
11 WHEREAS, the GYFT is intended to meet the educational needs of all who have a vested
12 interest in agriculture and seek to continue educational training; and
13 WHEREAS, the GYFT's mission is to provide educational, leadership, and networking
14 opportunities to agriculture education students and adults interested in agriculture, assisting
